AGI - The Israeli government is at work to establish a "migration administration" > to oversee the exodus of the population from Gaza. The Minister of Finance, Bezalel Smotrich, said this, addressing the Caucus Land of Israel of the Knesset. In his speech Smotrich emphasized that the question of the budget to create this specific administration "will not be an obstacle" to the realization of the task, that the minister has defined as logistically "complete".
According to the news site Ynet, the Minister of Insediaments and National Projects Orit Strock, a member of the extreme right-wing Zionism of Smotrich, said that the removal of the threat to security from Gaza cannot be reached "if not through a voluntary migration plan". >
In an interview released last month at "Meet the Press" on Channel 12, Smotrich had declared that Israel is actively in contact with Washington to discuss the implementation of the <a href="https://www.agi.it/estero/video/2025-02-26/video-virale-trump-gaza-30187846/"piano </a> videoestero
<h2> The withdrawal from the WHO
Israel could withdraw from the World Health Organization (Oms), following the footsteps of the United States after the measure launched by President Donald Trump. According to the Knesset website, tomorrow the Knesset Health Committee will hold a special debate on the " Israel retreat from the World Health Organization". The Times of Israel newspaper reports it. > The Walla news site predicted that the debate will be held at the request of the members of the Likud of Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu and the deputies of the extreme right-wing parties, religious Zionism and Otzma Yehudit.
<br> "The organization's policy is often contaminated by anti-Semitism > and by clear discrimination against Israel > and is a serious violation of the legitimacy of the State of Israel as a sovereign state," says Walla's legislators. The organization was very critical of Israeli military operations in Gaza, in particular Idf attacks on hospitals. Israel motivated such interventions by stating that Hamas and other Gaza terrorist groups were using hospitals as a basis for attack.
